@looeee Hi thanks for the reply. Do you mean in general or with morph targets? A few weeks ago I did some size tests and found ascii fbx to be larger than dae (at least in this instance and size is a concern for these projects). 

I've just done some more tests with the FBXLoader / Exporter and found I'm not getting morph targets or standard materials out (they default to unlit/basic) with the error "FBXLoader.js:206 No implementation given for material type [object Object] in FBXLoader.js." I've tried std blinn / std phong / dx shader.  

I also tried with exporting out to both Z and Y up and both are coming out the same (the usual 90 degree offset issue between Z/Y coord systems). Resetting the transforms doesn't seem to help. Point Cache modifiers get disabled at export (apparently it will disable all WSM modifiers). At least from my experiments so far I've found OpenCollada doesn't suffer these rotation issues and I hacked it's loader to read std phong mats as TJS PBR to make the process a little easier. Still it's far from ideal as it doesn't read lights, cams or (for me so far) morph targets and point cache data
